Probabilistic Methods, Neural Networks, Theory. 

Probabilistic Methods: The paper discusses the bias of learning devices, which can be seen as a probabilistic approach to learning. The authors also mention the use of probability distributions in modelling learning biases.

Neural Networks: The paper discusses generalist models of learning, which can be seen as a type of neural network. The authors also mention the isotropy of bias, which is related to the structure of neural networks.

Theory: The paper proposes a refinement of the notion of innateness, which can be seen as a theoretical contribution to the field of AI. The authors also discuss the characteristics of bias and how they relate to different types of learning models.
